<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,971,1120]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
The tergites of this species, which is the 
<typeStatus box="[626,677,971,997]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<emphasis box="[808,1027,972,997]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Scleropauropoides</emphasis>
Remy, 
<number box="[1117,1178,971,997]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="1957.0">1957</number>
, are somewhat granular and pleated but their setae are large, squamous, broad distally, and with large insertion areas. The pygidial sternum has the setae 
<emphasis box="[408,422,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">b</emphasis>
<number box="[422,430,1067,1081]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<emphasis box="[447,462,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">b</emphasis>
<number box="[462,470,1067,1081]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
, but no 
<emphasis box="[566,581,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">b</emphasis>
<number box="[580,588,1067,1081]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="3.0">3</number>
, and tergite V has 
<number box="[809,824,1051,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="4.0">4</number>
setae in the posterior row, not 
<number box="[1185,1203,1051,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="6.0">6</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
